gazing out of her window.. ♪

00:18.866 --> 00:20.800
(all)
Overton!

00:23.600 --> 00:25.733
Oh.

00:25.800 --> 00:27.566
Hello, ladies.

00:27.633 --> 00:31.633
Hello, you look like you
could use a little bit of TLC.

00:31.700 --> 00:32.800
‐ Hm.
‐ That's right.

00:32.866 --> 00:34.866
We thought we'd warm you up.

00:34.933 --> 00:36.866
Yeah, well, you're doin'
a marvelous job.

00:36.933 --> 00:39.466
I sweated clear through
to the box springs, girl.

00:41.866 --> 00:46.833
And we've got some ideas to
how to keep you warm all night.

00:46.900 --> 00:49.266
Oh, could you be thinking
about a little

00:49.333 --> 00:51.600
<i>menage a quatre?</i>

00:53.700 --> 00:57.400
Overton, man,
it is 1 o'clock in the mornin'.

00:57.466 --> 01:01.373
I've got a early meeting with
Japanese investors tomorrow

01:01.440 --> 01:05.340
and if I yawn,
then there will be no yen.

01:06.473 --> 01:08.406
Ah!

01:09.873 --> 01:12.673
Hey, man, what the hell
you're doing waking me up?

01:12.740 --> 01:16.640
Man, I'm dreaming
I was in bed with TLC, dude!

01:16.706 --> 01:19.806
And we were, we were getting
along quite nicely.

01:19.873 --> 01:21.573
Thank you very much.

01:21.640 --> 01:23.440
You know, that is better
than your usual dream

01:23.506 --> 01:25.473
of the dance
of the sugar plum hand drill.

01:26.740 --> 01:27.806
Oh, no, Kyle.

01:27.873 --> 01:31.573
I mean, me dreaming about TLC.

01:31.640 --> 01:33.873
What does that say
about Synclaire now?

01:33.940 --> 01:36.740
I mean, uh, am I unfulfilled?

01:36.806 --> 01:39.740
Do I like more fiber
in my spiritual diet?

01:41.073 --> 01:43.673
‐ Overton, you my cat, right?
‐ 'Mm‐hmm.'

01:43.740 --> 01:45.040
So, I am gonna
give your problem

01:45.106 --> 01:47.973
the appropriate
amount of thought.

01:48.040 --> 01:49.806
Finished. Goodnight.

